  {
   "itemId": "103",
   "html": "<p class=\"default-note\" _item_id=\"103\"><strong>NOTE:</strong> The agency sub-components displayed in this section were added to provide greater transparency into the organization of agencies’ account data. These sub-components are based on the Bureau associated with a federal account in OMB’s Master Accounts Title file. Sub-components are identified using Agency Identifier (AID) and MAIN Account codes. Where possible, Department of Defense (DoD) sub-components correspond to the branches of the Armed Forces and accounts for the agency are attributed t...</p>"
  },
  {
   "itemId": "104",
   "html": "<h3 _item_id=\"104\">Award Spending</h3>"
  },
  {
   "itemId": "105",
   "html": "<div class=\"section__date-note\" _item_id=\"105\">Data through 9/30/2025</div>"
  },
  {
   "itemId": "106",
   "html": "<div class=\"status-of-funds__intro-section-title\" _item_id=\"106\">How much is Department of Defense (DOD) spending on contracts and financial assistance?</div>"
  },
  {
   "itemId": "107",
   "html": "<div class=\"status-of-funds__intro-section-text\" _item_id=\"107\">Federal agencies use some portion of their<span class=\"status-of-funds__glossary-term\">budgetary resources</span> </div>"
  },
  {
   "itemId": "108",
   "html": "<div class=\"status-of-funds__intro-section-text\" _item_id=\"108\">for awards to recipients in the form of contracts and financial assistance. Each award consists of a roll-up of individual<span class=\"status-of-funds__glossary-term\">transactions</span> </div>"
  },
  {
   "itemId": "109",
   "html": "<div class=\"status-of-funds__intro-section-text\" _item_id=\"109\">, including transactions that obligate money. In this section, we show which sub-agencies of Department of Defense (DOD) have issued awards through different types of contracts or financial assistance and how much each sub-agency has obligated (promised to spend).</div>"
  },
